{{Infobox business park | name = International Business Park | image = | image_upright = | alt = | caption = Changi Business Park | map_type = Singapore | relief = | map_size = | map_dot_label = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location in Singapore | location = [[Jurong East]], [[Singapore]] | address = International Business Park Singapore | coordinates = {{coord|1|19|46.5|N|103|44|51|E|display=title}} | opening_date = July 1992 | closing_date = | developer = | construction_cost = | manager = [[JTC Corporation]] | owner = | architect = | number_of_tenants = | number_of_workers = | size = 37 hectares | parking = | website = | footnotes = }}
'''International Business Park''' ([[Abbreviation]]: '''IBP'''; {{lang-ms|Taman Perniagaan Antarabangsa}}; [[Simplified Chinese|Chinese]]: 国际商业园) is a high-tech business park managed by [[JTC Corporation]] in [[Jurong East]], [[Singapore]].
==Background== Established in 1992, the International Business Park is Singapore's first [[business park]]. It comprises a cluster of modern business buildings catering to knowledge-based activities. Some of the companies located at IBP include Acer Computer, [[Creative Technology|Creative]], [[Sony]], [[Dell]], [[MobileOne|M1]] as well as both the German Centre for Industry and Trade and the Nordic European Centre, which function as incubators for European start-up companies.
Honorary Consulate of [[Estonia]] is located on the 13th floor in one business building.
