{{notability|Biographies|date=March 2015}}'''Rinaldi Firmansyah''' (born 10 June 1960 in [[Tanjung Pinang]], [[Riau Islands Province|Riau Islands]]) is an Indonesian businessman.<ref name="RinaldiFirmansyahProfileForbes">{{ cite web| url = https://www.forbes.com/finance/mktguideapps/personinfo/FromPersonIdPersonTearsheet.jhtml?passedPersonId=942322| title = Rinaldi Firmansyah Profile| date =| publisher = Forbes.com}}{{dead link|date=September 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref>
== Education == Graduate of Electrical Engineering (Ir), [[Bandung Institute of Technology]] in 1985. Master of Business Administration (MBA), IPMI Jakarta. Chartered Financial Analyst (CFA), AIMR, Charlottesville, USA.
== Work experiences == CEO of [[Telkom Indonesia]] (until 2012). Director of Finance in [[Telkom Indonesia]]. Commissioner and Head of Audit Committee in [[Padang Cement|PT.Semen Padang]].
== Family == Firmansyah family came from [[Solok]], [[West Sumatera]]. His brother is Erry Firmansyah, the CEO of the [[Indonesia Stock Exchange]].
