{{Infobox company | name = Transnational Corporation of Nigeria plc | logo = | type = Conglomerate | industry = [[Energy]], [[Electric power|Power]], [[Hospitality]] | location = [[Lagos]], [[Lagos State]], Nigeria | key_people = {{unbulleted list |[[Tony Elumelu]], Group [[Chairman]] |[[Adim Jibunoh]], [[President/CEO]] |[[Tony Chukwueke]], Director,Tenoil Petroleum & Energy |[[Kalyana Sundaram]], [[CEO]], [[Transcorp Power Limited]] }} | products = Hotels, energy, power | homepage = http://www.transcorpnigeria.com }}
'''Transnational Corporation of Nigeria''' plc (or '''Transcorp'''), is a diversified conglomerate with strategic investments and core interests in the hospitality, agribusiness and energy sectors.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://theeconomyng.com/news39.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-03-15 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120722015442/http://theeconomyng.com/news39.html |archivedate=2012-07-22 |df= }}</ref> A publicly quoted conglomerate with a diversified shareholders base of about 290,000 investors, its notable assets include [[Transcorp Hotels plc]] (Transcorp Hilton Hotel, Abuja and Transcorp Hotels, Calabar); [[Teragro Commodities Limited]], Transcorp Ughelli Power Limited and Transcorp Energy Limited (operator of OPL 281).<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.proshareng.com/news/16229|title=Transcorp and Partners Revise Oil License Agreement|work=Transcorp and Partners Revise Oil License Agreement|access-date=2017-08-29|language=en}}</ref>
==Origin== Transnational Corporation of Nigeria plc was incorporated on November 16, 2004. The original concept was that Transcorp would be a conglomerate, similar to the South Korean Chaebols.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://theeconomyng.com/news39.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-03-15 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120722015442/http://theeconomyng.com/news39.html |archivedate=2012-07-22 |df= }}</ref>
==Transcorp's Businesses== {{buzzword|date=April 2015}}
*Transcorp Hilton Hotel, Abuja – a 670-room 4-star hotel.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www1.hilton.com/en_US/hi/hotel/ABUHITW-Transcorp-Hilton-Abuja/index.do|title=Abuja Hotels - Transcorp Hilton Abuja - Hotels in Abuja, Nigeria|website=www1.hilton.com|language=en|access-date=2017-08-29}}</ref> *Transcorp Hotels, Calabar – a 146-room destination hotel located in the city of Calabar, Cross River State, Nigeria.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.businessdayonline.com/New/index.php/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=48320:transcorp-hotels-unveils-a-new-n300m-facility-in-calabar&catid=185:hotel-a-resort&Itemid=636|title=New $250m fund to drive W/Africa’s technology development - BusinessDay : News you can trust|date=2013-12-03|work=BusinessDay : News you can trust|access-date=2017-08-29|language=en-US}}</ref> *Teragro Commodities Limited – the agribusiness subsidiary, operator of the Teragro Benfruit Plant, Benue State, Nigeria.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/transcorp-coming-out-of-the-woods/120265/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-02-27 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130411234017/http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/transcorp-coming-out-of-the-woods/120265/ |archivedate=2013-04-11 |df= }}</ref> Teragro Limited runs a juice concentrate plant in the Middle Belt area of Nigeria where the supply of agricultural raw materials are readily available. Its products are offered at a business-to-business enterprise model.<ref>http://lagosbusinessnews.com/node/388</ref> *Transcorp Energy Limited – established in 2008 for upstream petroleum exploration, operator of OPL 281. It is a fully owned subsidiary of Transnational Corporation of Nigeria that is active across the entire energy value chain.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.investadvocate.com.ng/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=3490:transcorp-sacoil-a-eer-revise-opl-281-license-agreement&catid=24:capital-market&Itemid=60|title=InvestAdvocate - Market News::...In Your Interest|website=InvestAdvocate|language=en-US|access-date=2017-08-29}}</ref> *Transcorp Power Limited (TPL) – the owner and operator of the Ughelli Power Plant which was privatised by the Nigerian government along with other Nigerian power assets. The plant has an installed capacity of 1000MW.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/transcorp-14-firms-sign-agreement-to-take-over-discos-gencos/140273/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-03-14 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130225004916/http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/transcorp-14-firms-sign-agreement-to-take-over-discos-gencos/140273 |archivedate=2013-02-25 |df= }}</ref> The plant is located in Delta State and had an available capacity of 480 MW as of November 2015. TUPL has made full payment of $300million for the plant.
==Acquisitions== *The Hilton, Hotel, Abuja: In December, 2005, Transcorp acquired 51% controlling stake in the Hilton Abuja for the sum of $105 million (equivalent at the time to N13.7billion) after a very competitive bid. The remaining 49% is owned by the Bureau of Public Enterprise (BPE).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://theeconomyng.com/news39.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-03-15 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120722015442/http://theeconomyng.com/news39.html |archivedate=2012-07-22 |df= }}</ref> *Rumens Road: Transcorp also acquired Rumens Road Apartments at 1 Rumens Road, Ikoyi, Lagos in 2005 for N377m.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://allafrica.com/stories/201006280117.html|title=Nigeria: Court Restrains FG, Transcorp From Evicting Tenants|last=Iriekpen|first=Davidson|date=2010-06-28|work=This Day (Lagos)|access-date=2017-08-29}}</ref> *Oil Blocs: Transcorp acquired two oil blocs in the May 2006 bidding round, consolidated in one oil bloc, OPL 281 . Ownership of the OPL 281 oil bloc, which had previously been revoked by the Department of Petroleum Resources, was returned to Transcorp in February 2011 after the payment of the balance of the signature bonus . Transcorp is partnering with Equity Energy Resources (EER), and pan-African energy company SAC-Oil Holdings of South Africa, to take equity and provide resources that will bring the oil bloc into operation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.investadvocate.com.ng/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=3490:transcorp-sacoil-a-eer-revise-opl-281-license-agreement&catid=24:capital-market&Itemid=60|title=InvestAdvocate - Market News::...In Your Interest|website=InvestAdvocate|language=en-US|access-date=2017-08-29}}</ref> *Metropolitan Hotel, Calabar: Transcorp acquired the 146-room Metropolitan Hotel in Calabar (now re-branded Transcorp Hotels Calabar) in June 2010.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thenigerianvoice.com/nvlifestyle/36179/16/transcorp-metropolitan-hotel-poised-to-up-hospital.html|title=Nigeria HomePage - Breaking News, Business, Sports, Entertainment and Video News|website=www.thenigerianvoice.com|access-date=2017-08-29}}</ref> *Benfruits Plant: On November 29, 2010, Transcorp signed a lease agreement with the Benue State Government for the Benfruits juice concentrate plant in Markurdi, Benue State.<ref>http://lagosbusinessnews.com/node/388</ref> *Ughelli Power Plant: On September 25, 2012, Transcorp Ughelli Power Limited (TUPL) (which comprises Wood Rock Energy Resources Limited, Symbion power LLC, Thomassen Holding Limited, Medea Development S.A., Tenoil Petroleum and Energy Services Limited and PSL Engineering and Control Limited) won the $300m bid for the acquisition of the Ughelli Power Plant, one of the six power generation companies of the Power Holding Company of Nigeria (PHCN) being privatised by the Federal Government of Nigeria. The Ughelli plant is a thermal power generating plant located in Delta State, Nigeria with installed capacity of 1000MW but currently producing 330MW which accounts for 8% of Nigeria's total power generation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ngrguardiannews.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=99799:transcorp-others-win-bids-for-five-power-plants&catid=1:national&Itemid=559|title=The Guardian Nigeria Newspaper – Nigeria and World News|website=www.ngrguardiannews.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-08-29}}</ref> On February 21, 2013, Transcorp representatives attended the official signing ceremony at the Presidential Villa in Abuja, Nigeria for the winning bidders of the privatisation of the PHCN. The ceremony was presided over by the Nigerian Minister of Power, Professor Chinedu Nebo and hosted by the Bureau of Public Enterprises (BPE).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.punchng.com/business/business-economy/nigeriansll-soon-enjoy-regular-electricity-supply-elumelu/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-02-27 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130226175926/http://www.punchng.com/business/business-economy/nigeriansll-soon-enjoy-regular-electricity-supply-elumelu/ |archivedate=2013-02-26 |df= }}</ref>{{relevance inline|date=April 2017}} TUPL met the 25 percent deposit deadline by paying the sum of US$75million to the BPE on March 20, 2013 and on August 21, 2013, TUPL made payment to the BPE of $225million, representing 75 percent of the $300million bid price for the 1000 megawatt capacity Ughelli Power Plant. On November 1, 2013, the Federal Government of Nigeria officially handed over the plant to Transcorp Ughelli Power Limited.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.vanguardngr.com/2013/11/transcorp-takes-ughelli-power-plant/|title=Transcorp takes over Ughelli power plant - Vanguard News|date=2013-11-04|work=Vanguard News|access-date=2017-08-29|language=en-US}}</ref>
==Recent Partnerships== On January 30, 2013, Transnational Corporation of Nigeria plc and General Electric (GE) signed a framework agreement to collaborate to address the infrastructural needs of Nigeria, with emphasis on the power and transportation sectors specifically rail transportation.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/general-electric-transcorp-target-650mw-from-ughelli-power-plant/137931/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-02-27 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130202184849/http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/general-electric-transcorp-target-650mw-from-ughelli-power-plant/137931 |archivedate=2013-02-02 |df= }}</ref> GE, a global leader in the design, manufacture, supply, installation and maintenance of technology and services for the power sector, confirmed its commitment to facilitate the generation of 10,000MW of additional power in Nigeria over the next decade in line with its existing agreement with the Federal Government of Nigeria, signed in March 2012.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/general-electric-transcorp-target-650mw-from-ughelli-power-plant/137931/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-02-27 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130202184849/http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/general-electric-transcorp-target-650mw-from-ughelli-power-plant/137931 |archivedate=2013-02-02 |df= }}</ref>
